[Amit Varma]: what what does it propose to do like I'm trying to imagine a future landscape in which this

03:23:11.440 --> 03:23:15.880
[Amit Varma]: problem is solved or at least in which this problem is not such a big problem yes it won't

03:23:15.880 --> 03:23:21.960
[Guest]: be solved fully but to a large extent there will be an independent regulatory body with

03:23:21.960 --> 03:23:25.640
[Guest]: an initial corpus of hundred crores of its own to conduct statistical research and so

03:23:25.640 --> 03:23:31.280
[Guest]: on so on the one hand it will innovate and produce new kinds of statistics on the other

03:23:31.280 --> 03:23:37.080
[Guest]: it will be a new sort of regulator of the statistical system so what think of the think

03:23:37.080 --> 03:23:44.080
[Guest]: of it as the CAG of the statistical system so it will audit all the government department

03:23:44.080 --> 03:23:48.840
[Guest]: it will examine whether the processes that exist today to collect data whether it be

03:23:48.840 --> 03:23:55.200
[Guest]: for an Anganwadi whether it be for COVID deaths whether it be for IIP or whether it be for

03:23:55.200 --> 03:23:59.720
[Guest]: GDP so it will look at all this there will be different departments or different members

03:23:59.720 --> 03:24:04.160
[Guest]: look looking into each of this and they will evaluate whether certain core principles of

03:24:04.160 --> 03:24:08.640
[Guest]: statistics are being followed whether certain transparency principles are being followed

03:24:08.640 --> 03:24:12.880
[Guest]: and they will publish all their findings and this thing in a transparent they will be accessible

03:24:12.880 --> 03:24:17.040
